           on every authenticated user; absent on inbound trunk traffic. The
           outbound-telnyx and local-ext extensions in context.xml refuse to
           bridge unless this is "true", so an attacker who reaches the
           dialplan via spoofed From URIs from the public internet cannot
           reach the outbound bridge even if a destination regex slips. -->
      <variable name="sip_authorized" value="true"/>
    </variables>
